In sum, High Voltage better satisfies the concrete production and songwriting attributes I value — punchy low end, guitar‑first sonic identity, aggressive solos, and cohesive, robustly mastered album sequencing — while Déjà Vu’s vocal‑centric, softer, and more acoustic/ballad‑oriented character conflicts with my stated dislikes.

